id: pm-pz7xtx
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2F: classify manifest-proven torn bundle call-time TypeError"
description: Sentry PM-CLI-2F captured registerOperationCommands is not a function during CLI operation-family bootstrap. The existing bundle-integrity boundary recognizes missing-module and missing-export loader errors but not the equivalent call-time shape caused by a mixed bundle generation. Extend diagnosis only when the manifest proves the generation changed or files are missing/hash-invalid; intact bundles must preserve the original TypeError.
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-21T20:19:20.366Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:31:10.937Z"
assignee: codex
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: TDD covers changed-generation and intact-manifest call-time TypeError paths; focused and full 100/100/100/100 coverage pass; packed installed CLI operation smoke passes; live Sentry/telemetry gate returns zero critical/high blockers after resolution.
parent: pm-u9d0
severity: high
environment: production
expected_result: Manifest-proven mixed bundle generations produce bundle_integrity_torn_install; intact runtime TypeErrors remain genuine blocking failures.
actual_result: PM-CLI-2F remained an unresolved high because the call-time 'is not a function' shape bypassed the diagnostic matcher.
affected_version: 2026.7.21
component: cli-bundle-bootstrap
regression: false
customer_impact: A concurrent/partial install can abort CLI startup without the actionable reinstall diagnostic and blocks the release reliability gate.
