comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T20:19:20.366Z",codex,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for Sentry PM-CLI-2F, torn bundle, registerOperationCommands, and call-time TypeError. No exact item exists. Closed pm-wfvq remains the completed canonical manifest-diagnostic implementation; this item records a newly observed error-shape gap and links that lineage plus standing release-health reminder pm-7zs0."
  "2026-07-21T20:20:40.912Z",codex,"TDD evidence: the new PM-CLI-2F regression failed before implementation because the call-time TypeError returned undefined; after extending the candidate error-shape matcher, all 8 focused tests pass. Classification remains fail-closed because an intact manifest returns undefined and only manifest-proven generation drift or file integrity failure emits bundle_integrity_torn_install."
  "2026-07-21T20:31:10.937Z",codex,"Verification evidence: pnpm build and the full static quality gate passed; all 334 test files and 6072 tests passed with literal all-source coverage at 100% statements (40971/40971), branches (28813/28813), functions (8317/8317), and lines (39850/39850). A packed tarball installed into /tmp/tmp.GMtlHlGpWu successfully ran init, create, list-open, and health --check-only with one intact item/history stream and zero integrity or lock warnings, directly exercising operation-family registration from the consumer artifact."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T20:31:09.987Z",codex,Bundle-generation races can surface after module loading as call-time TypeErrors when a stale importer receives a changed export shape. Candidate-message matching may include this shape safely only behind the existing atomic manifest proof; message text alone must never classify or suppress it.
